  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "225 lakh bail for Arjuna Aloysius",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "W. M. Colombo Additional Magistrate T. to release one of the directors of the company, Arjuna Aloysius and Jinendra John, who appeared in the court for non-payment of 167 crores of tax owed to the Inland Revenue Department by Mendis and the company, on bail of 225 lakh rupees. N. L. Mr. Ilangasinghe ordered today (02).",
        "Accordingly, W. No. 309/5, Negombo Road, Welisara has been released on bail. M. Mendis and two directors of the company.",
        "The Magistrate also ordered the suspects to discuss with the prosecution how to pay the defaulted income tax amount and inform the court on the next day.",
        "W. M. Last year 2021, the Inland Revenue Department had filed two cases before the court that Mendis and the company had failed to pay an amount of Rs. 1,678,795,049/= as income tax due to the Inland Revenue Department."
      ],
